#' getConfusion
#'
#' @usage getConfusion(dfA, dfB, inds, idColA, idColB = NULL)
#'
#' @param dfA First data frame being linked
#' @param dfB Second data frame being linked
#' @param inds A nx2 index pair matrix indicating the detected matches
#' @param idColA The column name of the shared id across dfA and dfB
#' @param idB What to concatenate to a column name in dfB if there exists a identical column in dfB
#'
#'
#' @return \code{bindMatches} returns a dataframe of the original dataframes bound by index.
#'
#' @author Sam Murray<slmurray@andrew.cmu.edu>
#' @export
#' @import tidyverse
